The paper deals with the problem of localizing target nodes in a mobile sensor network using range measurements and anchor nodes with GPS position information. This problem is closely related to robotics (cs.RO) and control systems (cs.SY) as it involves coordinating the movements of multiple sensors to achieve a common goal. The optimization techniques used in the paper also suggest a connection to mathematical optimization (cs.MA) and information theory (cs.IT). Finally, the paper uses simulations to validate its algorithms, which suggests a connection to computer vision (cs.CV).
